<!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html>
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8">
				
		<!-- Cascading style sheets, for formatting -->
		<!-- jQueryMobile CSS for mobile styling -->
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquerymobile/1.4.0/jquery.mobile.min.css" />
		 
		<!-- Custom styling -->
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="blinkylight.css" />
		
		<!-- Javascript libraries -->
		<!--  jQuery library
			  Use Google CDN when possible, since it is very common, and 
		      will probably already have downloaded to user's device.  
		      Scripts are generally cached by the device once downloaded,
		      with each CDN seen as unique, even if the script is the same.  -->
		<script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.9.1/jquery.min.js"> </script>
		
		<!-- jQueryMobile for mobile widgets -->
		<script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquerymobile/1.4.0/jquery.mobile.min.js"></script>
		
		<!--  D3 library.  For graphics. Not available through Google CDN  -->  
		<script src="http://d3js.org/d3.v3.min.js"> </script>
		
		<!-- Custom javascript -->
		<script src="blinkylight.js"> </script>
		
		<title> Light Simulator </title>
	</head>

	<body>
	
		<!-- Header -->
		<header data-role="header"> 

		</header>		
 		
 		<!-- Content -->
 		<div class="content">
 			<div id="mapcontainer" class="container">
 				<div id="map"> 
		
				</div>
 			</div>


			<div id="formcontainer" class="container">
				<div>  <p> This demo shows a light / sensor pair governed by 
				two thresholds.  Thrashing (repeated on/off) may occur depending 
				on the thresholds and the proximity of the light to the sensor. </p>   
			
				<p> Try changing the on / off thresholds and click "submit". </p>
				
				<p> The light source is 800 lumens (e.g. 60W incandescent).<br>  
				    The light source and sensor are moveable. </p>
				</div>
				<form name="form" id="form" accept-charset="UTF-8" 
					action="room" method="post">
					<p>	
						<label for="onThreshold">Turn on below (lumens):</label>
						<input type="range" name="onThreshold" 
							id="onThreshold" value="0" min="0" max="1000" 
							step="10" data-highlight="true" />			
					</p>
					
					<p>	
					  <label for="offThreshold">Turn off above (lumens):</label>
						<input type="range" name="offThreshold" 
							id="offThreshold" value="400" min="0" max="1000" 
							step="10" data-highlight="true" />			
					</p>
					<p>
						<input type="button" id="submit" name="submit" 
							value="Submit" />
					</p>		
				</form>		
			</div>
		</div>
	
		<!-- Footer -->
		<footer data-role="footer" data-theme="z" data-position="fixed">
			<img src="PtolemyIISmallIcon.gif" alt="Ptolemy II" 
				width="25" height="25" class="ui-btn-left"> 
				 <div class="footertext"> Powered by Ptolemy II,  
					http://ptolemy.eecs.berkeley.edu/ </div> 
		</footer>
	
	</body>
</html>
